# AMENDMENT artifact — a rule appended to a skill in response to an incident or cross-pattern.
# Usage: copy to docs/sdlc/amendments/AMD-<n>.yaml. Generated by the amendment-writer subagent.
# Amendments persist forever; the system NEVER deletes one (only supersedes via a new amendment).

id: AMD-001
triggered_by: incident           # incident | cross-pattern
  # `incident` — single failure event prompts this rule.
  # `cross-pattern` — drift-detector found the same class of mistake across N tasks.
target_skill: tdd-workflow       # the skill name (matches .claude/skills/<name>/SKILL.md)
rule: |                          # required, the new constraint phrased as instruction-to-agent
  Before declaring a failing test "expected to fail," confirm the assertion targets
  the production code path actually exercised by the test, not a sibling export.
applies_when: |                  # required, the trigger condition for this rule
  Test file imports more than one production module, OR test name and target function
  name diverge by more than two tokens.
severity: high                   # low | medium | high — high amendments block the gate
